"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1148441","Department for Transport","false","2019-10-08","<p>The benefits of the scheme were calculated over a 60-year period. The discount rate applied to the forecasted benefits was 3.5% each year for the first 30 years and 3% each year for the next 30 years, as stipulated in the HM Treasury’s “The Green Book: Central Government Guidance on Appraisal and Evaluation</p>",,"Baroness Vere of Norbiton",,"2019-10-08T15:49:19.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1148441/answer","Biography information for Baroness Vere of Norbiton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1148441/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1148441/answer",,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-10-07","M4","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government, further to the Written Answer by Baroness Sugg on 4 April (HL14781), what discount rate they applied to the forecasted benefits.","false","Biography information for Lord Lipsey",,"Lord Lipsey","HL18044"
