"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1148335","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-10-08","<p>The United Kingdom National Screening Committee in 2017 considered an evidence review of screening for Vasa Praevia (VP). The review did not find sufficient evidence to support a change in the overall recommendation for VP screening. The 2017 review can be seen at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://legacyscreening.phe.org.uk/vasapraevia" target="_blank">https://legacyscreening.phe.org.uk/vasapraevia</a></p><p> </p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2019-10-08T10:48:14.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1148335/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1148335/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1148335/answer",,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-10-04","Vasa Praevia: Screening","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what plans he has to introduce routine screening in pregnancy for Vasa Praevia.","false","Biography information for Laura Smith","Crewe and Nantwich","Laura Smith","294750"
