"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1148216","Treasury","false","2019-10-08","<p>While the UK is an EU member state the UK continues to be bound by State aid rules.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has taken repeated action to reduce the burden of business rates for all ratepayers, including those in the hospitality sector.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2019-10-08T07:59:38.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1148216/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1148216/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1148216/answer",,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-10-03","Service Industries: Non-domestic Rates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent assessment he has made of the effect of the application of state aid rules to business rates on the hospitality sector.","false","Biography information for Steve Double","St Austell and Newquay","Steve Double","294197"
