"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1148243","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-10-08","<p>There are differing views on trophy hunting imports, which is why the British Government recently announced plans to launch a consultation on further restricting the import and export of hunting trophies to and from the UK. In addition, the UK continues to work hard within international forums, such as the Convention on International Trade in Endangered Species of Wild Fauna and Flora (CITES), to ensure that wildlife is used in a sustainable and well managed way.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2019-10-08T13:06:07.113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1148243/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1148243/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1148243/answer",,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-10-03","Animal Products: Imports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what diplomatic steps he is taking to end trophy hunting imports throughout the world.","false","Biography information for Mrs Pauline Latham","Mid Derbyshire","Mrs Pauline Latham","294136"
