"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1148252","Treasury","false","2019-10-08","<p>The government has no current plans to introduce a small spirits relief. However, all taxes are kept under review and the impact of such a change is considered at each fiscal event; including its effect on the industry and wider economy.</p>","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Mr Simon Clarke",,"2019-10-08T07:22:30.23Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1148252/answer","Biography information for Mr Simon Clarke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1148252/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1148252/answer",,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-10-03","Spirits: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, what plans he has to reduce the rate of duty on spirits distilled by smaller distilleries in the UK.","false","Biography information for Graham P Jones","Hyndburn","Graham P Jones","294132"
