"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147829","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-10-08","<p>The Department does not keep official statistics on food bank use, so no such assessment has been completed. Some food aid providers produce statistics on the number of food parcels distributed, but the Government has no plans to require individual food banks to keep records as this would place a significant burden on charitable and voluntary organisations.</p><p> </p><p>We have listened to feedback on how we can improve Universal Credit to support our claimants and acted quickly, making improvements such as extending advances, removing waiting days, and introducing housing benefit run on. These changes are giving support to vulnerable people who need it most, whilst at the same time helping people get into work faster.</p><p> </p><p>Furthermore, in Scotland, the Department delivers Universal Credit Scottish choices on behalf of the Scottish Government, providing the option of Universal Credit being paid twice a month rather than monthly, and having Universal Credit housing element being paid directly to landlords.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Colchester","Will Quince",,"2019-10-08T10:07:32.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147829/answer","Biography information for Will Quince","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147829/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147829/answer",,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-10-02","Universal Credit: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent assessment she has made of the effect of the time taken for universal credit payments to be made to claimants on trends in the level of food bank use in Scotland.","false","Biography information for Hugh Gaffney","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Hugh Gaffney","293692"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147830","Scotland Office","false","2019-10-08","<p>I have regular discussions on important Scottish economic matters with my Cabinet colleagues, including the Chancellor of the Exchequer.</p><p> </p><p>Technology has transformed banking for millions of people, but we know that many still rely on cash. That is why we are co-ordinating work across government, regulators and industry so we can protect access for everyone who needs it.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>LINK, the scheme that runs the UK’s ATM network, has publicly committed to maintain the broad geographic spread of ATMs and has put in place specific arrangements to protect remote free-to-use ATMs one kilometre or further from the next nearest free-to-use ATM. More recently, LINK has committed to protecting free access to cash on high streets – where there is a cluster of five or more retailers – that do not have a free-to-use ATM or a Post Office counter within 1 kilometre.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Dumfries and Galloway","Mr Alister Jack",,"2019-10-08T15:04:00.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147830/answer","Biography information for Mr Alister Jack","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147830/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147830/answer",,,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2019-10-02","Cash Dispensing: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what recent discussions he has had with the Chancellor of the Exchequer on ensuring that people are able to access free-to-use cash machines throughout Scotland.","false","Biography information for Hugh Gaffney","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Hugh Gaffney","293693"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147831","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-10-08","<p>The organisations and amounts paid are set out below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Organisation</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Service</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Spend to date from public purse including VAT</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Big Ideas Community Interest Company</p></td><td><p>Community engagement</p></td><td><p>£69,296</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Dp9</p></td><td><p>Planning services</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Four Communications</p></td><td><p>Communications</p></td><td><p>£70,748</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Newgate Communications</p></td><td><p>Communications</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2019-10-08T16:03:18.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147831/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147831/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147831/answer",,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-10-02","National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 9 September to Question 286103 on Holocaust Memorial and Learning Centre, if he will name the organisations outside Government providing (a) public relations or engagement, (b) public affairs and (c) planning services in respect of the proposed Holocaust Memorial and Learning Centre; and how much is being paid from the public purse to each organisation.","false","Biography information for Sir Edward Leigh","Gainsborough","Sir Edward Leigh","293452"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147832","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-10-07","<p>Widespread deployment of 5G and full fibre networks is a primary objective of Government policy. The Government published the Telecoms Supply Chain Review in July, which recommended the introduction of a new framework for telecoms security based on evidence and a hard-headed assessment of the risks. The Government has not yet made a final decision on individual high risk vendors and the additional controls that will be applied to them. Our international partners must take their own approach based on their own circumstances, network architectures, capabilities and risk assessments.</p><p>The United States of America and the United Kingdom are natural, resilient and strong partners and allies, and we will continue to work closely together, including on the issue of telecoms security.</p>","Tamworth","Christopher Pincher",,"2019-10-07T15:11:25.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147832/answer","Biography information for Christopher Pincher","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147832/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147832/answer",,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-10-02","Huawei: 5G","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions the Government has had with the US Government on shared intelligence on Huawei's proposed role in developing the UK's 5G network.","false","Biography information for Graham P Jones","Hyndburn","Graham P Jones","293530"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147833","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-10-08","<p>UK Holocaust Memorial Foundation members Mr Peter Freeman and Mr Gerald Ronson CBE were members of the property sub-committee.</p><p> </p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2019-10-08T16:02:04.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147833/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147833/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147833/answer",,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-10-02","National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 31 July to Question 280921 on National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service, which individuals were members of the property sub-committee of the UK Holocaust Memorial Foundation from November 2015 to January 2016.","false","Biography information for Sir Edward Leigh","Gainsborough","Sir Edward Leigh","293453"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147834","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-10-08","<p>I refer my Rt Hon Friend to the answer to Question UIN 270267 of 27 June 2019, and remind the Rt Hon Gentleman that CBRE was only one element in the search for potential sites.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2019-10-08T16:00:33.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147834/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147834/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147834/answer",,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-10-02","National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 31 July to Question 280917 on National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service, for what reason sites identified by means other than the CBRE were not brought to the CBRE’s attention to enable it to compare all potential sites.","false","Biography information for Sir Edward Leigh","Gainsborough","Sir Edward Leigh","293454"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147835","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-10-08","<p>To carry out an extensive search for potential sites for the Holocaust Memorial and Learning Centre in line with the criteria set by the UK Holocaust Memorial Foundation.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2019-10-08T16:00:49.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147835/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147835/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147835/answer",,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-10-02","National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what the terms of reference were for the CBRE’s search for potential sites for the Holocaust Memorial and Learning Centre.","false","Biography information for Sir Edward Leigh","Gainsborough","Sir Edward Leigh","293455"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147836","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-10-08","<p>As set out in the answer to Question UIN 229625 on 14 March 2019, almost 50 sites were identified by a wide range stakeholders and considered by the UK Holocaust Memorial Foundation during the latter part of 2015.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2019-10-08T16:03:51.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147836/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147836/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147836/answer",,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-10-02","National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 31 July to Question 280917 on National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service, how many potential sites not among sites identified by the CBRE were identified by (a) Royal Parks, (b) Holocaust commemorative and educational organisations, (c) property owners and developers, (e) property agents, (f) London Borough authorities, (g) universities (h) museums and (i) cultural centres; and on what dates those potential sites were reported to the UK Holocaust Memorial Foundation.","false","Biography information for Sir Edward Leigh","Gainsborough","Sir Edward Leigh","293456"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147837","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-10-08","<p>The approach prior to appointment of CBRE is described in paragraphs 4.1.1-4.1.4 of the environmental statement.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2019-10-08T15:59:51.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147837/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147837/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147837/answer",,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-10-02","National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 4 July to Question 270267 on National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service, for what reason paragraphs 4.20 to 4.23 of the Planning Statement submitted by his Department to Westminster Council do not refer to the elements in the property search other than that by the CBRE.","false","Biography information for Sir Edward Leigh","Gainsborough","Sir Edward Leigh","293457"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147838","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-10-08","<p>At its meeting on 13 January 2016 the Foundation reviewed the progress of the site search and concluded that there could be no better site than Victoria Tower Gardens to place the Holocaust Memorial.</p><p> </p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2019-10-08T15:55:53.67Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147838/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147838/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147838/answer",,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-10-02","National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 31 July to Question 280917 on National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service, how many sites in addition to the 24 identified by the CBRE were considered by the board of the UK Holocaust Memorial Foundation for the first time on 13 January 2016.","false","Biography information for Sir Edward Leigh","Gainsborough","Sir Edward Leigh","293458"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147839","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-10-08","<p>Question UIN 280920 tabled by the Rt Hon Member for Gainsborough on 23 July 2019 was capable of inadvertently misrepresenting the government’s January 2016 statement. The answer sought to remove any ambiguity.</p><p> </p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2019-10-08T16:01:22.963Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147839/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147839/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147839/answer",,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-10-02","National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 31 July 2019 to Question 280920 on National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service, for what reason that Answer did not provide the information requested on communications with Royal Parks.","false","Biography information for Sir Edward Leigh","Gainsborough","Sir Edward Leigh","293459"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147840","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-10-07","<p>DCMS Ministers have regular discussions with the Foreign and Commonwealth Office on a range of cyber security topics, including in relation to the UK’s telecommunications networks.</p><p> </p><p>Widespread deployment of 5G and full fibre networks is a primary objective of Government policy. The Government published the Telecoms Supply Chain Review in July, which recommended the introduction of a new framework for telecoms security based on evidence and a hard-headed assessment of the risks. The Government has not yet made a final decision on individual high risk vendors and the additional controls that will be applied to them.</p>","Boston and Skegness","Matt Warman",,"2019-10-07T12:43:17.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147840/answer","Biography information for Matt Warman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147840/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147840/answer",,,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-10-02","Huawei: 5G","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what recent discussions she has had with the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs on shared intelligence from the US Government on Huawei's proposed role in developing the UK's 5G network.","false","Biography information for Graham P Jones","Hyndburn","Graham P Jones","293531"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147841","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-10-08","<p>The Foundation has yet to complete its consideration of options.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2019-10-08T16:01:46.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147841/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147841/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147841/answer",,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-10-02","National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 31 July to Question 280914 on National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service, if he will publish the operating models the United Kingdom Holocaust Memorial Foundation is considering to cover the running costs of the Holocaust Memorial and Learning Centre.","false","Biography information for Sir Edward Leigh","Gainsborough","Sir Edward Leigh","293460"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147842","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-10-08","<p>The search for possible sites began in July 2015.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2019-10-08T16:02:27.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147842/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147842/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147842/answer",,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-10-02","National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answers of 15 and 31 July 2019 to Questions 274442 and 280922 on National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service, on what date in November 2015 the property sub-committee of the UK Holocaust Memorial Foundation was asked to undertake a search of Government sites.","false","Biography information for Sir Edward Leigh","Gainsborough","Sir Edward Leigh","293461"
