"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147844","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-10-08","<p>In common with other public places in Westminster there will be no security checks for visitors to Victoria Tower Gardens.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2019-10-08T15:57:00.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147844/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147844/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147844/answer",,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-10-02","National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, if he will make it his policy not to introduce security checks for visitors to Victoria Tower Gardens other than people visiting the Memorial and Learning Centre after that centre has opened.","false","Biography information for Sir Edward Leigh","Gainsborough","Sir Edward Leigh","293463"
