"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147892","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-10-07","<p>The Mechanised Infantry Vehicle programme is currently under review and a decision is expected this year. If a contract is placed, it is anticipated that circa 60% by value of the contract spend will be with UK suppliers.</p>","Berwick-upon-Tweed","Anne-Marie Trevelyan",,"2019-10-07T16:22:26.673Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147892/answer","Biography information for Anne-Marie Trevelyan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147892/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147892/answer",,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-10-02","Armoured Fighting Vehicles: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when he will announce the procurement timetable for the Mechanised Infantry Vehicle programme; and what proportion of the build will be undertaken domestically.","false","Biography information for Ruth Smeeth","Stoke-on-Trent North","Ruth Smeeth","293667"
